Remarks. Excepting
C. acuticerca
,
C. giganea
is also “aberrant” in this genus; this species was described based on one specimen lacking an abdomen from Perak , Malaysia ( Roth 1993 ). It’s distinctly different from other
Ctenoneura
species by its pronotum and venation, with a body distinctly larger than any known
Ctenoneura
species. Due to only the single and incomplete example described in Roth (1993) , the generic status of this species remains unsolved; we have included it in
Ctenoneura
temporarily.
